ðŸŸ© Problem

Youâ€™re managing a task list where each task has a unique ID.
A new task must be inserted at a specific position in the linked list.
If the position is valid, insert the task and print the updated list.
If the position is invalid, print:
Position out of range

---

ðŸŸ© Input Format

1. N â€” number of task IDs
2. N space-separated task IDs
3. P â€” position to insert at (1-based)
4. M â€” new task ID

---

ðŸŸ© Sample Input

```
4
101 102 103 104
2
999
```

ðŸŸ© Sample Output

```
101 999 102 103 104
```

---

ðŸŸ© Solution

import java.util.*;

public class Solution {

    class Node {
        int data;
        Node next;

        Node(int data) {
            this.data = data;
            this.next = null;
        }
    }

    class Linkedlist {
        Node head = null;

        void insertAtPosition(int pos, int value) {
            Node newnode = new Node(value);

            // If inserting at the beginning
            if (pos == 1) {
                newnode.next = head;
                head = newnode;
                return;
            }

            Node curr = head;
            for (int i = 1; i < pos - 1; i++) {
                if (curr == null) {
                    System.out.print("Position out of range");
                    return;
                }
                curr = curr.next;
            }

            if (curr == null) {
                System.out.print("Position out of range");
                return;
            }

            newnode.next = curr.next;
            curr.next = newnode;
        }

        void build(int data) {
            Node newnode = new Node(data);

            if (head == null) {
                head = newnode;
                return;
            }

            Node curr = head;
            while (curr.next != null) {
                curr = curr.next;
            }
            curr.next = newnode;
        }

        void print() {
            Node curr = head;
            while (curr != null) {
                System.out.print(curr.data + " ");
                curr = curr.next;
            }
        }
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        int n = sc.nextInt();
        Solution obj = new Solution();
        Linkedlist ll = obj.new Linkedlist();

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            ll.build(sc.nextInt());
        }

        int pos = sc.nextInt();
        int value = sc.nextInt();

        ll.insertAtPosition(pos, value);
        ll.print();
    }
}
```

ðŸŸ© Time Complexity -O(n) â€” [We may traverse the list up to the insertion point once â†’ O(n)]
ðŸŸ© Space Complexity - O(n) â€” [Storing n nodes in the linked list]
